Introduction

DGNA (previously known as The B.O.S.S) is a three-member group that made their debut in March of 2010 with the song "Admiring Boy."

The group initially had five members: Mika, Karam, Hyunmin, Injun, and Jay. However, Mika and Hyunmin later parted ways with the group around 2018.

In February of 2023 they participated in the show Peak Time as Team 23:00 but chose to leave the show after the 3rd round.

On December 21, 2023 KST, New Ways Company announced that it has signed an exclusive contract with former DGNA members Karam, Injun, and Jay.
According to New Ways Company, "Karam, Injun, and Jay will form a new group with additional members and return with new music in the first half of 2024."
